<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,903,1144]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Described originally in 
<taxonomicName box="[425,521,904,928]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Euthrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[425,521,904,928]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Euthrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this thrips is here newly recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[999,1070,903,927]" name="Brazil" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, although it is found widely on various plants between 
<collectingCountry box="[419,475,940,964]" name="United States of America" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">USA</collectingCountry>
and South 
<collectingCountry box="[607,707,940,964]" name="United States of America" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">America</collectingCountry>
. As in 
<taxonomicName box="[790,893,940,964]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Frankliniella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="williamsi">
<emphasis box="[790,893,940,964]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">williamsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this yellow species is unusual in having discal setae on abdominal sternite II. However, the differences between these two species are small, and they are distinguished from each other only by the length of the setae on the ninth abdominal tergite (
<bibRefCitation author="Mound" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="Mound, L. A. &amp; Marullo R. (1996) The Thrips of Central and South America: An Introduction. Memoirs on Entomology, International, 6, 1 - 488." type="journal article" year="1996">
Mound &amp; Marullo 
<number box="[151,211,1047,1071]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1996.0">1996</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The specimens examined from Bahia have the setae S 
<number box="[831,842,1047,1071]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1.0">1</number>
and S 
<number box="[910,925,1047,1071]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2.0">2</number>
on abdominal tergite IX measuring 
<number box="[1327,1355,1047,1071]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="70.0">70</number>
and 
<number box="[1408,1436,1047,1071]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="75.0">75</number>
microns long, respectively.
</paragraph>
